OL,3,CTories urge Government to step in as
OL,4,CMiddlesbrough Council faces bankruptcy
OL,6,FConservative politicians are calling
OL,7,Ffor the government to take control of
OL,8,Fa North East council facing bankruptcy.
OL,10,FMiddlesbrough Council, which is
OL,11,Fcurrently Labour-run, says it needs to
OL,12,Ffind a way to plug its #6.3 million
OL,13,Ffunding gap.
OL,15,FIn a letter to Parliament, Simon
OL,16,FClarke MP and Tees Valley Mayor Lord
OL,17,FHouchen, both of the Conservative
OL,18,Fparty, have formally requested the
OL,19,Fgovernment intervenes in the running
OL,20,Fof the local authority "before matters
OL,21,Fdeteriorate further".
